Someone on Tumblr asked: How do you translate &quot;gigil&quot; to English? Usually refers to an overwhelming urge to do something.
The &ldquo;something&rdquo; is implied by the context, for example if the &ldquo;gigil&rdquo; is directed at something cute, the urge is usually to pinch, i.e.
Tagalog: &ldquo;Ang cute ng baby mo, nakakagigil!&rdquo;
English: &ldquo;Your baby is so cute, I have an overwhelming urge to pinch him!&rdquo;
Can also be directed at something frustrating/annoying.
